page.title: 20CONCLUSION, S.E., IPSWICH
page.content: As these pages have revealed, this area of Ipswich has a great variety of land-use.It is both urban and rural, growing and declining.The area is dominated by it's estuary of the river Orwell and magnificent views of the area around this stretch of water can be gained by the new bridge. The great variety of scenery and the hussle and bussle of life in this area proved to be very interesting to the pupils at both Copleston school and st.Johns Primary.It is largely through the pupils efforts that this information has been gained . All the typing and computer entries were made by three pupils at Copleston Tara Palmer,Lisa Adams and Zoe Forrest under guidance of their teacher,Mr Leeder.
